        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 3:39AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 339 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms from southeastern Nolan County, southeast into
northeastern Runnels County and southwestern Coleman County..
Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winters, Noodle, Lawn, Ballinger, Bradshaw, Hatchel, Abilene, Caps,
Impact, Hylton, Lake Abilene, Ovalo, Wingate, Hodges, Ivie Reservoir
Near Concho Park Marina, Drasco, Coronados Camp, Pumphrey, and Lake
Winters Lake.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 258 and 287.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
